About the Episode:
The Second in a trio of new one-off sitcoms under the banner of Comedy Playhouse, the long-running BBC 
anthology from the 1960s and 1970s that launched such programmes as Steptoe and Son, Last of the Summer Wine 
and Are You Being Served? 
Jimmy Chisholm stars as Jimmy Miller, the leader of a motley gang of mountain rescue volunteers, 
who is showing the ropes to new volunteer Conor on his first day, an initiation that naturally begins in 
the pub, where characters include no-nonsense barmaid Jules (Sharon Rooney, My Mad Fat Diary).
